                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=postalservice14",
                        "name": "postalservice14",
                        "displayName": "John Kelly",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Well it IS passing the PDO exception as the previous exception for exception chaining. (Geez, how many times can I say exception in a sentence).  So the PDO's error code and message should be passed along in the chain and printed out in the stack trace right?\r\n\r\nBesides that information all PDO\\Statement really knows is that the execution failed.  IDK, I think the exception message is fine.\r\n\r\nWhat do you think?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=postalservice14",
                        "name": "postalservice14",
                        "displayName": "John Kelly",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-08-21T14:44:53.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-08-21T14:44:53.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/51655",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Try doing this:\r\n\r\n{code}\r\ntry {\r\n  \/\/... something that fails\r\n} catch (Exception $e) {\r\n  $pdoException = $e->getPrevious();\r\n  var_dump($pdoException);\r\n}\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nIf you are using the ZFSkeleton Application, it should be designed to show you any previous exceptions that might have occurred.",
